text: Klepp is a municipality in Rogaland County, Norway, located in the Jæren district. Established in 1838, it covers 113.49 km² and has a population of about 20,600 (2023). The administrative center is Kleppe. Known for its flat farmland and beaches, Klepp is a major agricultural hub. It is also home to the Kverneland Group, a global manufacturer of agricultural equipment. Category:Norway
title: Klepp
